WEBVTT

00:00:06.961 --> 00:00:09.741
Listen...
I have an idea.

00:00:10.061 --> 00:00:13.801
Yeah. My little sister is really fast at
this stuff.

00:00:14.141 --> 00:00:15.901
Seriously?
As fast as my wife.

00:00:16.121 --> 00:00:19.221
Her name's Aki, so just ask for Aki's
number and get it out fast.

00:00:19.301 --> 00:00:21.042
Just spit it out.
Bang bang bang, like that...

00:00:22.162 --> 00:00:24.582
Forget about Dad for now.
No, but my dad's...

00:00:25.042 --> 00:00:29.482
No, listen, you're gonna have your sister
ask your dad's body count?

00:00:29.502 --> 00:00:32.482
That's insane.
No way.

00:00:32.482 --> 00:00:36.223
We need to go that far.
No, that's not it.

00:00:36.523 --> 00:00:41.023
You ask your own dad's body count.
Your dad is so damn slow.

00:00:41.383 --> 00:00:42.483
So we're doing this?
No, no, no.

00:00:42.663 --> 00:00:46.143
Seriously, Bryant cries at the drop of a
hat. Yeah, okay.

00:00:46.323 --> 00:00:47.464
It connected, it connected.
All right.

00:00:49.958 --> 00:00:51.030
Will my dad actually say it?
Go investigate.

00:00:51.030 --> 00:00:56.164
Okay. Hello? Hello? Mom? It's Shinichi.

00:00:57.044 --> 00:01:00.384
Shinichi? Yeah, it's me. Sorry, sorry, I'm
at a pay phone.

00:01:00.384 --> 00:01:03.545
Yeah. Asking for Aki's number like this
really makes me sound like a scammer.

00:01:03.585 --> 00:01:05.885
I need Aki's number right away,
so please tell me.

00:01:05.965 --> 00:01:08.485
What happened? Why are you calling this
much?

00:01:08.485 --> 00:01:14.086
Just for a second, please, hurry.
Sorry. Wait a sec.

00:01:17.266 --> 00:01:19.286
Uh, hold on a sec.
Oh, Osaka area code.

00:01:19.286 --> 00:01:20.966
Fast. Fast, huh. Here it comes. Okay. 080,
080.

00:01:20.966 --> 00:01:23.446
Yeah. 080-XXXX-XXXX. Yeah. Okay, is Dad
there? Dad's...

00:01:24.606 --> 00:01:30.147
He's already in the car on his way here.

00:01:31.027 --> 00:01:33.887
Ah, okay, got it. Dad.
Right.

00:01:33.887 --> 00:01:37.187
Okay, sorry. Sorry about that.
Dad...

00:01:37.227 --> 00:01:39.047
Dad was out.
Ah.

00:01:40.247 --> 00:01:41.448
Ah.
Okay.

00:01:41.528 --> 00:01:45.068
She could ask your mom for you too.
Yeah, but it's fine.

00:01:45.068 --> 00:01:48.468
At least you got Aki's number.
Now what?

00:01:49.788 --> 00:01:52.188
How do we get out?
Right here.

00:01:53.048 --> 00:01:54.829
OK Google, help me.
I'm not getting anywhere.

00:01:54.889 --> 00:01:59.789
Get me out of the dirt.
Sorry, I didn't understand that.

00:02:01.069 --> 00:02:03.689
How do you not understand this situation?
No hint at all.

00:02:03.809 --> 00:02:05.709
This is miserable and scary.
OK Google.

00:02:08.790 --> 00:02:12.910
Tell me something fun.
Then here's a riddle.

00:02:13.030 --> 00:02:16.230
Oh?
A boxer and a diamond.

00:02:17.190 --> 00:02:21.951
What's the connection?
Both shine in the ring.

00:02:22.241 --> 00:02:23.241
Ohhh.
Ah.

00:02:26.511 --> 00:02:29.371
It even adds a laugh track?
No, that was good.

00:02:30.851 --> 00:02:33.931
Should we call Makio?
Let's call Makio already.

00:02:33.931 --> 00:02:37.652
Want to try him?
First we need to decide what to ask Makio.

00:02:37.652 --> 00:02:39.612
Um, ask Makio...
Ueno Zoo.

00:02:40.252 --> 00:02:41.632
Yeah.
Ueno Zoo, and...

00:02:41.892 --> 00:02:42.892
NHK, and...
Rakuen.

00:02:42.892 --> 00:02:47.212
Damn...
Kamata Depart.

00:02:47.292 --> 00:02:52.873
Whoa, that's brutal. What are you making a
King of Conte champion do?

00:02:52.933 --> 00:02:57.853
Makio went to Waseda,
so he probably knows smart people.

00:02:57.933 --> 00:03:00.653
Should we ask him the one about one to a
million? Let's ask that first.

00:03:02.274 --> 00:03:04.274
Please, Makio's...
Yeah.

00:03:07.214 --> 00:03:12.054
Makio might be in the middle of curry
right now. Hello?

00:03:12.054 --> 00:03:13.394
Hello?
Is this Mr. Makio?

00:03:15.075 --> 00:03:16.075
Yeah.
It's Minamikawa.

00:03:16.075 --> 00:03:20.395
Yeah, yeah, what's up? Makio, you went to
Waseda, right? Were you science?

00:03:21.475 --> 00:03:22.475
Yeah.
No, arts.

00:03:22.475 --> 00:03:25.275
Arts, huh?
Don't just assume.

00:03:25.355 --> 00:03:27.935
What an unprovoked comeback.
A call from a junior...

00:03:28.796 --> 00:03:31.876
A junior calls you up
and goes, 'Arts, huh?'

00:03:32.696 --> 00:03:34.836
Makio, uh, at Ueno Zoo...
Yeah.

00:03:36.026 --> 00:03:37.026
The flamingos...
Yeah.

00:03:37.896 --> 00:03:41.456
Can you find out how many there are?
Sure.

00:03:41.576 --> 00:03:43.297
Yeah, I can look it up.
Seriously?

00:03:44.137 --> 00:03:46.777
Ueno Zoo. Okay, then, I'll call you back
in 15 minutes.

00:03:46.797 --> 00:03:49.777
Yeah, yeah, okay.
He's so nice.

00:03:49.877 --> 00:03:52.917
No, no, no, no.

00:03:57.226 --> 00:03:59.326
Can't be helped.
You're too slow, Minamikawa-san.

00:04:00.026 --> 00:04:01.826
Since earlier.
What do you mean?

00:04:01.826 --> 00:04:04.426
He was arts, okay?
Well, that can't be helped.

00:04:04.646 --> 00:04:08.966
You two make a living talking crap about
people. Of course you'll clash.

00:04:08.966 --> 00:04:12.667
Next you're stuck with Minamikawa for
hours. Don't cave, man.

00:04:13.547 --> 00:04:16.527
To that kind of stuff.
What else can I do?

00:04:18.167 --> 00:04:21.807
Didn't you both come from Osaka Shochiku?
Oh, really?

00:04:22.287 --> 00:04:24.287
Oh, nice.
Nice, nice.

00:04:24.767 --> 00:04:29.547
All we can do is keep eating.
Gross.

00:04:29.547 --> 00:04:30.747
Ugh, no, no.
Ugh, no.

00:04:31.827 --> 00:04:33.487
Nice. Gross, ugh. Nice. Nasty.
Hate it.

00:04:33.487 --> 00:04:34.807
I hate this.
Still, we're getting somewhere.

00:04:34.907 --> 00:04:36.787
This is the only way.
It hits your

00:04:36.787 --> 00:04:38.628
brain stem.
Hard.

00:04:38.668 --> 00:04:39.808
The sweetness.
Hahahaha.

00:04:39.868 --> 00:04:44.308
So sweet. This is what happens when you
eat too much candy.

00:04:45.268 --> 00:04:47.008
Like chocolate cream.
You're losing it.

00:04:47.008 --> 00:04:48.794
Hmm.
This might be bad.

00:04:49.988 --> 00:04:52.848
This might be bad too.

00:04:52.917 --> 00:04:54.559
No, I want a black coffee.
Yeah, true.

00:04:54.708 --> 00:04:57.208
Yeah.
Hmm.

00:04:57.328 --> 00:05:00.868
Man, black coffee would be great.
I wonder if they have coffee jelly.

00:05:00.928 --> 00:05:03.348
This is seriously rough.
It could count as hydration too.

00:05:03.448 --> 00:05:07.129
Hydration, yeah.
This isn't some rich-person game anymore.

00:05:08.289 --> 00:05:11.129
It's like that diamond game.
I mean, it looks like a dream world.

00:05:11.389 --> 00:05:14.269
Then they drag us into this gross room
and make us eat candy.

00:05:14.309 --> 00:05:18.729
When you think about it, a candy house
would suck. It really would.

00:05:18.789 --> 00:05:19.909
Yeah.
It sounds all fairy-tale-like, but...

00:05:19.929 --> 00:05:22.589
Hello?
Ah, Makio, sorry.

00:05:23.009 --> 00:05:26.089
Did you figure out the flamingos?
Yeah, I did.

00:05:26.309 --> 00:05:32.529
You did? How many were there?
Well, this is from 2017, though.

00:05:32.709 --> 00:05:34.310
From 2017?
Just the info, yeah.

00:05:34.350 --> 00:05:36.090
Yeah.
Okay.

00:05:36.810 --> 00:05:39.190
It said 40.
Forty?

00:05:39.410 --> 00:05:45.130
An older article said...
uh, 31.

00:05:45.350 --> 00:05:48.410
So what are we supposed to do with that?
But the newer info says 40.

00:05:49.110 --> 00:05:50.250
Come on.
Forty?

00:05:50.250 --> 00:05:52.390
Got it. I'll call you again then, sorry.
Okay.

00:05:52.390 --> 00:05:53.270
Sorry about that.
Yeah.

00:05:53.270 --> 00:05:57.950
That's why I hate this.
Makio...

00:05:58.830 --> 00:06:00.070
He did look it up for you.
Yeah.

00:06:00.971 --> 00:06:03.171
You can't say that.
He has no idea what's going on.

00:06:03.171 --> 00:06:06.031
Not to someone who helped you.
That attitude is messed up.

00:06:06.791 --> 00:06:08.471
Makio really...
This is hopeless.

00:06:08.551 --> 00:06:10.651
Aki is perfect, though.
No, I mean...

00:06:11.591 --> 00:06:15.131
I trust my sister.
Let's just say it once.

00:06:15.471 --> 00:06:17.071
Yeah.
At Ueno Zoo,

00:06:17.071 --> 00:06:20.001
