Like, some kind of cigarette...

00:06:58.653 --> 00:07:03.753
Is there a brand name that wouldn't
instantly read as cigarettes?

00:07:04.773 --> 00:07:07.153
Then something like Mevius.
Mevius.

00:07:07.153 --> 00:07:11.473
Mevius is a real word too. Or Wakaba,
maybe that wouldn't give it away.

00:07:11.473 --> 00:07:12.473
Wakaba.
What do you actually want to smoke?

00:07:13.033 --> 00:07:15.553
Marlboro Gold.
I'd be fine with that too.

00:07:15.553 --> 00:07:16.553
Huh?
Honestly.

00:07:16.693 --> 00:07:18.713
What?
Really, I'd want Lucky Strike.

00:07:19.193 --> 00:07:21.273
That's a strong one.
Damn.

00:07:21.373 --> 00:07:23.494
But Marlboro...
like Red Marl or...

00:07:24.034 --> 00:07:26.494
Gold Marl, stuff like that exists.
Yeah.

00:07:26.494 --> 00:07:30.694
Yeah, that might actually be better.
Amazing how even in this situation...

00:07:31.774 --> 00:07:35.794
you still crave cigarettes this much.
No, I kind of get it.

00:07:35.874 --> 00:07:37.034
Because I smoke.
Ah, right.

00:07:37.354 --> 00:07:40.734
When it comes down to it, what I want is a
cigarette. That's where I end up.

00:07:41.274 --> 00:07:42.854
Even in this situation.
Even in this situation.

00:07:42.854 --> 00:07:43.854
A cigarette?
Yeah.

00:07:45.194 --> 00:07:50.355
'Hatara-ku.' Yeah, I guess 'cigarettes'
would give it away. No, I'd still be fine.

00:07:51.155 --> 00:07:52.575
Let's go with 'Hatara-ku.'
Yeah.

00:07:53.255 --> 00:07:55.315
Might rank
above food at this point.

00:07:55.495 --> 00:07:56.975
Once it gets to this point...
Seriously?

00:07:57.015 --> 00:07:58.275
'Hatara-ku.'
'Hatara-ku.'

00:07:58.375 --> 00:08:01.635
We could also do 'kido airaku.'
Which one's better?

00:08:01.635 --> 00:08:04.115
That's nice, that kind of one.
Yeah, I'm good with pun names.

00:08:04.235 --> 00:08:07.915
How about 'kido airaku'?
Want to try that?

00:08:08.355 --> 00:08:09.895
It does have 'Lark' in it.
And it's cute.

00:08:10.275 --> 00:08:11.635
Cute.
Let's go with 'Kido Airaku.'

00:08:11.635 --> 00:08:13.895
Yeah, that's good.
And tell Makio to

00:08:14.635 --> 00:08:15.735
